<!-- // DUSTWORM RECRUITMENT // -->
<event name="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM" unique="true"> <!-- Event 1: Theocracy Badlands -->
    <text>Upon the stony, sandswept planet below, you can see an Outcast settlement. Its buildings are crumbled and dilapidated, likely the result of an attack or a natural disaster.</text>
    <img planet="PLANET_UNPOPULATED_TERRA"/>
    <choice>
        <text>Land on the planet.</text>
        <event>
            <text>Other than some poor weather on its way towards the colony, you encounter no resistance on your way to the surface. As soon as you land your vessel, a group of Outcasts and a Lost Sun quietly approach your group, urging you to come closer.</text>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event>
                    <text>"Careful now, traveler... this planet is quite dangerous! We've heard tales of sandworms out here, massive things that can feel your steps upon the sand a mile away! Our best team of explorers went missing a couple of days ago, and the day after, it burrowed through our streets and knocked down several of our buildings. Suffice to say, we've called off that mission until we can get another team in order to rescue them.</text>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Offer your help repairing the settlement.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Although you can't do much, especially with the fleet crawling down your back as always, the Outcasts appreciate the help you're able to offer.</text>
                            <autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Explore the sands yourself.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Although the Outcasts laugh at your proclamation, they do offer you directions towards the last known location of their exploration team, and you and your crew set out into the sands. If the colony sent an exploration team out here, perhaps there was something they were looking for. You make sure to tread lightly in the hopes of not aggravating whatever these sandworms are, but signs of an oncoming sandstorm and the blazing heat of the sun tell you it might be more difficult than you expected.</text>
                            <choice hidden="true">
                                <text>Continue to explore, knowing the Rebel Fleet may catch up.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>It's difficult to navigate the sandstorm, let alone push your body forwards through the blistering wind and abrasive particles. Tremors from the earth and movement in the nearby sands suggest sandworm activity, though your steps are thankfully quiet enough to avoid rousing them. Your crew struggle similarly, eventually stumbling through the dunes to find the remains of a small Chrysolic temple. Though heavily eroded by the relentless sandstorms, it still serves as a good shelter, and likely was the location the Outcast explorers were trying to reach.</text>
                                    <modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
                                    <choice hidden="true">
                                        <text>Continue...</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER"/>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                            <choice req="LIST_CREW_ROCK" hidden="true">
                                <text>(Rock Crew) Have your Rock lead the way.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>With the large frame and high resilience of your crewmember acting as a shield, navigating the sand is at least slightly less time-consuming. Soon, you find the remains of a small Chrysolic temple. Though heavily eroded by the relentless sandstorms, it still serves as a good shelter, and likely was the location the Outcast explorers were trying to reach.</text>
                                    <choice hidden="true">
                                        <text>Continue...</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER"/>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                            <choice req="LIST_CREW_CRYSTAL" hidden="true">
                                <text>(Crystal Crew) Have your Crystal lead the way.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>With the large frame and high resilience of your crewmember acting as a shield, navigating the sand is at least slightly less time-consuming. Soon, you find the remains of a small Chrysolic temple. Though heavily eroded by the relentless sandstorms, it still serves as a good shelter, and likely was the location the Outcast explorers were trying to reach.</text>
                                    <choice hidden="true">
                                        <text>Continue...</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER"/>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Return to the colony.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>With sand thoroughly suffusing your outfit and your body, you return to the colony in defeat. Even so, being willing to walk out into the stirring sands and the hot sun earns you a smile from the Commando on your way back to the ship.</text>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Sorry, we can't help.</text>
                        <event/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>We don't have time.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You steer away from the planet, flying out to orbit.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Do nothing.</text>
                <event/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER">
    <text>The temple is mostly filled with simple relics and artworks. Few things here are actually worth any scrap, but they seem like they'd be quite valuable to Theocracy-aligned Rockmen. As you turn a corner, rumbles and shaking sound out through the walls, and a large mound of sand begins to move as an odd squeaking sounds from behind it!</text>
    <choice hidden="true" max_group="0">
        <text>Shoot it!</text>
        <event>
            <text>A single shot is all that it takes to stop the movement, blue goo leaking from the small hole left behind. The collapsing sand releases a couple of Rockmen, who are resilient enough to get back up after a successful resuscitation procedure. Unfortunately, more rumbles from around the temple suggest it's too dangeous to stay for much longer, the sound of your weapon having likely stirred up more sandworms to hunt you down. Your return to the colony is bittersweet, with a funeral held for the remaining expedition members. Even so, the colony offers you a few supplies as thanks.</text>
            <autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="aa_found_dustworm" lvl="0" max_group="1">
        <text>Wait for the sand to fall away.</text>
        <event name="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER_GOOD"> <!-- Update when Dustworms are implemented as a faction to make their description more direct.-->
            <text>As the sand settles to the floor, it reveals a strange, caterpillar-like alien who tumbles to the floor in a daze. The streaming particles also release a couple of Rockmen, who are resilient enough to get back up after a successful resuscitation procedure. This was certainly not the kind of sandworm the Outcasts told you about, and the now-found exploration team doesn't recognize them either, but they do their best to aid in the search for remaining members of the team. Your return to the colony is triumphant, with the colony thankful and the alien offering to join your crew!</text>
            <autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
            <crewMember amount="1" class="aa_dustworm"/>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="aa_found_dustworm" lvl="1" max_group="1">
        <text>Wait for the sand to fall away.</text>
        <event name="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER_DUSTWORM">
            <text>As the sand settles to the floor, it reveals a Dustworm who tumbles to the floor in a daze. The streaming particles also release a couple of Rockmen, who are resilient enough to get back up after a successful resuscitation procedure. This was certainly not the kind of sandworm the Outcasts told you about, and the now-found exploration team doesn't recognize them either, but they do their best to aid in the search for remaining members of the team. Your return to the colony is triumphant, with the colony thankful and the Dustworm offering to join your crew!</text>
            <autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
            <crewMember amount="1" class="aa_dustworm"/>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="LIST_CREW_SLUG" hidden="true" max_group="2">
        <text>(Slug Crew) Your Slug crew shouts to hold your fire!</text>
        <event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
    </choice>
    <choice req="BLUELIST_CREW_SNAIL" hidden="true" max_group="3">
        <text>(Telepathic Shell) Your Shell crew shouts to hold your fire!</text>
        <event load="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER_GOOD"/>
    </choice>
    <choice req="LIST_CREW_MONK" hidden="true" max_group="4">
        <text>(Monk Crew) Your Monk urges you to relax.</text>
        <event load="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER_GOOD"/>
    </choice>
    <choice req="AA_LIST_CREW_DUSTWORM" hidden="true" max_group="5">
        <text>(Dustworm Crew) Your Dustworm recognizes the squeaking.</text>
        <event load="AA_EVENT_OUTCAST_SANDWORM_DISCOVER_DUSTWORM"/>
    </choice>
</event>

<ship name="AA_SHIP_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION" auto_blueprint="MU_SEPARATIST_SCOUT_NOCREW">
    <triggeredEvent name="AA_SHIP_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_SURRENDER_TRIGGER" event="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_SURRENDER" thisFight="true">
        <enemyHull amount="0" min="4" max="4" scaling="0.0"/>
    </triggeredEvent>
	<destroyed load="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_DESTROYED"/>
</ship>
<event name="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION" unique="true"> <!-- Event 2: Emancipated Sanctuary -->
    <text>There is a single, battered Separatist ship at the beacon, and it hails you the moment you show up. "F-F-F-Federation vessel? You must help! Ship is [infested] with a virus, I am on the -outside- and trying to regain control. Have taken command of c-c-c-communications, but more is difficult. Can you help remove the infestation?"</text>
    <ship load="AA_SHIP_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION" hostile="false"/>
    <choice>
        <text>Accept.</text>
        <event>
            <text>"Thank you." The Separatist cuts the communications, and the threatened ship raises its weapons and automated defenses to protect itself!</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="hacking">
        <text>(Hacking) Attempt to purge the "virus."</text>
        <event>
            <text>Your Hacking system finds not only no trace of corrupted code, but a very angry rudimentary artificial intelligence system. The ship attempts to defend itself!</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="BLUELIST_WEAPONS_HACK">
        <text>(Hacking Weapon) Attempt to purge the "virus."</text>
        <event>
            <text>Your Hacking weapon only aggravates a very angry rudimentary artificial intelligence system. The ship attempts to defend itself!</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="LIST_CREW_SLUG">
        <text>(Slug Crew) Your Slug has something to say.</text>
        <event>
            <text>As your Slug takes the stage, they explain to the Engi that they sense a number of caterpillar-like life-forms in the walls of the ship. They aren't quite familiar in nature, but they are not hostile, and seem to have damaged some of the circuitry in their attempts to hide.</text>
            <choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_SURRENDER_SKIP"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="BLUELIST_CREW_SNAIL">
        <text>(Telepathic Shell) Your Shell has something to say.</text>
        <event>
            <text>As your Shell takes the stage, they explain to the Engi that they sense a number of caterpillar-like life-forms in the walls of the ship. They aren't quite familiar in nature, but they are not hostile, and seem to have damaged some of the circuitry in their attempts to hide.</text>
            <choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_SURRENDER_SKIP"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="LIST_CREW_HARMONY">
        <text>(Harmony Engi) Your Engi has something to say.</text>
        <event>
            <text>Your Engi attempts to take the stage, but the Separatist gets panicky and slams the outside of the ship. This causes its weapons to spring to life!</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Decline.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You apologize and cut comms.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Do nothing.</text>
                <event/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_SURRENDER">
    <text>As your shots rock the hull, the ship hails again. The voice that comes out over the waves isn't the stutter of a Separatist Engi, but of a much lighter, more organic nature. "Stop, stop! What did they tell you to do!?"</text>
    <choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="aa_found_dustworm" lvl="0" max_group="0">
        <text>They told us to "remove the infestation."</text>
        <event>
            <text>The strange voice manages to get the camera working, revealing a group of small, caterpillar-like creatures peering through cracks in the wall. "N-no, we had no other choice! This was the only ship we could find, we ended up with a bunch of pirates who wanted to get rid of us... I thought the robot-thing would do the same!"</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Explain the situation to the Separatist.</text>
                <event name="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_SURRENDER_SKIP">
                    <text>"What? This... i-i-i-is..." The Engi, having managed to force their way in through the airlock, is completely stunned, not sure what to do about the situation. A couple of the braver aliens begin to crawl out of panels in the wall, squeaking out and staring at the red figure in the center of the room. "I-I-I-I thought it was a -virus-... what to do [now]?" The Engi, and the creatures, stare at you.</text>
                    <ship hostile="false"/>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Suggest the creatures come with you.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Still somewhat afraid, the insects nod, waiting in the room as you dock with your ship. They all board your ship, relieved to be out of the situation, and hide out in the cargo bay until you drop them off at a nearby station with many curious eyes. On the way, a couple of them have the handiness to help fix up your hull, and one of them even wants to join you on your journey through the stars!</text>
                            <crewMember amount="1" class="aa_dustworm"/>
                            <damage amount="-7"/>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Suggest the Engi coexists with the creatures.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Although the bugs are concerned, you, your crew, and the Engi are able to help calm them down and fully describe the misunderstanding. The Separatist is quite grateful that you were able to help solve the issue, and is quite curious about these... "dustworms." In return, they offer a number of useful supplies and a spare weapon!</text>
                            <autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
                            <weapon name="GIFTLIST_ION"/>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="aa_found_dustworm" lvl="1" max_group="0">
        <text>They told us to "remove the infestation."</text>
        <event>
            <text>The strange voice manages to get the camera working, revealing a group of Dustworms peering through cracks in the wall. "N-no, we had no other choice! This was the only ship we could find, we ended up with a bunch of pirates who wanted to get rid of us... I thought the robot-thing would do the same!"</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Explain the situation to the Separatist.</text>
                <event name="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_SURRENDER_SKIP">
                    <text>"What? This... i-i-i-is..." The Engi, having managed to force their way in through the airlock, is completely stunned, not sure what to do about the situation. A couple of the braver Dustworms begin to crawl out of panels in the wall, squeaking out and staring at the red figure in the center of the room. "I-I-I-I thought it was a -virus-... what to do [now]?" The Engi, and the Dustworms, stare at you.</text>
                    <ship hostile="false"/>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Suggest the Dustworms come with you.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Still somewhat afraid, the Dustworms nod, waiting in the room as you dock with your ship. They all board your ship, relieved to be out of the situation, and hide out in the cargo bay until you drop them off at a nearby station with many curious eyes. On the way, a couple of them have the handiness to help fix up your hull, and one of them even wants to join you on your journey through the stars!</text>
                            <crewMember amount="1" class="aa_dustworm"/>
                            <damage amount="-7"/>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Suggest the Engi coexists with the Dustworms.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Although the Dustworms are concerned, you, your crew, and the Engi are able to help calm them down and fully describe the misunderstanding. The Separatist is quite grateful that you were able to help solve the issue, and is quite curious about them. In return, they offer a number of useful supplies and a spare weapon!</text>
                            <autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
                            <weapon name="GIFTLIST_ION"/>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Ignore the communication.</text>
        <event>
            <text>"Wait, STO-" The voice is shut off, and you continue to attack the ship. It may not be what the Separatist wanted, but it'll still benefit you.</text>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_SEPARATIST_INFESTATION_DESTROYED">
    <text>The ship breaks apart, though you also seem to have destroyed the Separatist owner clinging to its hull. You can scrap the remains at your leisure, though it isn't much.</text>
    <autoReward level="LOW">scrap</autoReward>
</event>

<event name="AA_EVENT_ORCHID_GREENHOUSE" unique="true"> <!-- Event 3: Gathering Gardenworlds -->
    <text>There is a Gathering station at the beacon. Several visible greenhouses mounted to it offer a good view of several growing pieces of technology, though they seem worse for wear and some of the plants are damaged. Though there is a Caretaker ship docked to it, the station does not respond to your presence.</text>
    <ship load="SHIP_ORCHID_STATION" hostile="false"/>
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>Dock with the station.</text>
        <event>
            <text>The halls are empty, but well-lit and kept maintained. A soft, floral scent wafts through the air, crossing with the pungent scent of spores. It doesn't take long to find the staff, who are all huddled in the corner of a safe room. "You have to help us! Our kernel growths are being devoured by monsters!"</text>
            <choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="aa_found_dustworm" lvl="0" max_group="0">
                <text>Inspect the greenhouses.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>A Caretaker among the staff hands you the keycard to open the greenhouses. The heat and humidity flow out, revealing several big, blue worms devouring the plants! The one closest to you notices your arrival, squeaking out. "W-wait, wait! Who are you? I thought this place was abandoned!"</text>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>You're eating weaponry.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>The alien calms down as you explain the situation to them, their stare of fear quickly being replaced by one of embarrassment. The others turn to listen to the conversation, the sounds of crunching throughout the room ceasing and leaving a dead silence. Although it's tough, you're able to coax the Orchids into working out a negotiation, and nudge the worms into vacating the station. The Orchids offer you one of the few uneaten Kernel weapons being grown aboard as thanks, and one of the bugs offers to join you instead of being dropped off.</text>
                            <crewMember amount="1" class="aa_dustworm"/>
                            <weapon name="GIFTLIST_KERNEL"/>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Get out of there!</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>You brandish your weapon. The strange worms panic and swarm out of the room, throughout the station. Hunkering down wherever they can, it quickly becomes clear that flushing them out will take more time than you have. The Caretakers will have to find help elsewhere.</text>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Not my problem.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>You promptly shut the door, leaving the greenhouse alone. The Caretakers will have to find help elsewhere.</text>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="aa_found_dustworm" lvl="1" max_group="0">
                <text>Inspect the greenhouses.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>A Caretaker among the staff hands you the keycard to open the greenhouses. The heat and humidity flow out, revealing several Dustworms devouring the plants. Thankfully, since you know what they are, you are able to defuse the situation and lead them out of the greenhouse. The Orchids offer you one of the few uneaten Kernel weapons being grown aboard as thanks, and one of the bugs offers to join you instead of being dropped off.</text>
                    <crewMember amount="1" class="aa_dustworm"/>
                    <weapon name="GIFTLIST_KERNEL"/>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice hidden="true" req="AA_LIST_CREW_DUSTWORM" max_group="1">
                <text>(Dustworm Crew) The Orchids seem to be huddled further away from your crew.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>Noticing their reaction, your Dustworm speaks up. It doesn't take long for the situation to calm down, and it quickly becomes obvious from the Orchids' descriptions of the situation that a small group of other Dustworms managed to infest the greenhouse without knowing what they were eating. After they clear out from the greenhouse, the Orchids offer you one of the few uneaten Kernel weapons being grown aboard as thanks, and one of the bugs offers to join you instead of being dropped off.</text>
                    <crewMember amount="1" class="aa_dustworm"/>
                    <weapon name="GIFTLIST_KERNEL"/>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice max_group="2">
                <text>I'm sorry, we can't help.</text>
                <event/> <!-- This one piece of the event was such a nightmare, I did not know choices required an empty event if no leave text was displayed. -->
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Attack!</text>
        <event>
            <text>You raise your weapons, and the station responds in kind. The Gathering won't be very happy about this.</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_ORCHID_FIGHT"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Avoid the station.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You keep clear of the station. Best not to mess with an Orchid greenhouse.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Do nothing.</text>
                <event/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>




