<event name="AA_EVENT_DUSK_IMAGINATOR" unique="true">
    <distressBeacon/>
    <text>You arrive at the beacon. In spite of the oppressive Duskbringer presence here, several Union and Ministry ships have established a trading post around it, their colorful hulls gleaming in the light of a distant sun. A Peacekeeper stands guard, as most of the vessels are unarmed.</text>
    <ship load="AA_SHIP_ZOLTAN_IMAGINATOR" hostile="false"/>
    <customFleet right="false" firing="false" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_CIVILIAN</customFleet>
    <choice req="aa_found_imaginator" lvl="0" hidden="true" max_group="0" blue="false"> <!-- Have not found this event yet -->
        <text>Hail the traders.</text>
        <event>
            <variable name="aa_found_imaginator" op="set" val="1"/> <!-- This event cannot yield the loot outcome more than once per run. -->
            <text>Out of all the ships, it is the Peacekeeper that responds directly to your hail. An old Zoltan in heavy armor responds in an uncharacteristic panic. "Oh, thank goodness! You're military, right? Renegade, even?"</text>
            <choice>
                <text>That would be us.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>"Couldn't be a better time for you to show up! Some of our salvage crew's run into a stretch of territory the Rebels have taken... they've been taken hostage! My son's in danger!" He steps back from the panel, clutching his head. "Oh, Great Eye, will you help? The Ministry wants me to stay here... but how can I!?"</text>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Agree to help.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>"Thank you! Goodness, I'll send over the co-ordinates right away!" He sprints off to a corner of the room, and transfers a string of numbers. "T-they were salvaging our old trading post... a candy store. Why would those pricks go after a bunch of civvies salvaging an un-militarized station? I-it doesn't make sense! P-please, save my son!" The hyperventilating captain is led away by his crew, presumably to the medbay, as the other ships open their doors to you.</text>
                            <quest event="AA_EVENT_QUEST_IMAGINATOR"/>
                            <store>STORE_STANDARD</store>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Decline.</text>
                        <event name="AA_EVENT_FILLER_IMAGINATOR_DECLINE">
                            <text>"Drat!" The captain slams his fist on his console, accidentally cutting the feed. At least the other ships at the beacon offer some rather lucrative trade deals for your trouble.</text>
                            <store>STORE_STANDARD</store>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Nope.</text>
                <event load="AA_EVENT_FILLER_IMAGINATOR_DECLINE"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="aa_found_imaginator" lvl="1" hidden="true" max_group="0" blue="false"> <!-- Already found this event -->
        <text>Hail the traders.</text>
        <event>
            <text>A sense of deja-vu resonates within you as you approach the traders. However, the Peacekeeper doesn't make a move to hail you. Just a few vessels open to trade this time, it seems.</text>
            <store>STORE_STANDARD</store>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="1" blue="false" hidden="true">
        <text>Attack the station!</text>
        <event>
            <text>You open fire on the trading post. Most of the civilian vessels are unarmed - the only ship with enough weapons to contest you here is the Ministry envoy. Hopefully, they have enough scrap to make it worthwhile...</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_UNION_FIGHT"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="2" blue="false" hidden="true">
        <text>Leave them be.</text>
            <event>
			<text>You have no need for trade right now.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
    </choice>
</event>

<ship name="AA_SHIP_REBEL_IMAGINATOR" auto_blueprint="AA_SHIP_REBEL_IMAGINATOR">
	<destroyed load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_IMAGINATOR_WIN"/>
    <deadCrew load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_IMAGINATOR_WIN"/>
</ship>
<event name="AA_SHIP_REBEL_IMAGINATOR_FLARES">
	<text>As its weapons spring from its hull, the MFK Ace fires off a set of tracking flares. They shine lights onto your ship, disrupting your ability to cloak!</text>
	<status type="loss" target="player" system="cloaking" amount="3"/>
	<triggeredEvent event="AA_SHIP_REBEL_IMAGINATOR_FLARES_END" time="20" thisFight="false" clearOnJump="true">
		<triggeredEventBox load="DEFAULT_SMALL" pos="combat">
			<tooltip>The enemy's cloaking jammer will expire in this amount of time.</tooltip>
		</triggeredEventBox>
        <timerSounds load="DEFAULT_TIMER_SOUNDS"/>
	</triggeredEvent>
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>Continue...</text>
        <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_SHIP_REBEL_IMAGINATOR_FLARES_END">
	<text>The flares fade into the background of space. Your systems have returned to normal.</text>
	<status type="clear" target="player" system="cloaking" amount="100"/>
</event>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_IMAGINATOR">
    <beaconType id="map_icon_quest" global="true">
		<color r="69" g="168" b="235" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>You've been tasked with searching for hostages at a candy store.</unvisitedTooltip>
	</beaconType>
    <text>The instant you arrive at the beacon, it becomes clear something is wrong. In front of you lies the derelict station, as expected, but the civilian vessel you were sent for is currently being accosted by an MFK Dropship Ace and a pair of Auto-ships. Why would some of the highest-profile Rebels in their forces terrorize random civilians?</text>
    <ship load="AA_SHIP_REBEL_IMAGINATOR" hostile="false"/>
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>Rescue the civilians.</text>
        <event>
            <text>The Ace's captain reeks of a stuck-up attitude, his voice dripping with contempt. "Hoho, a Renegade has come to interfere with our operation? I don't think so, not today. That cache is mine!" If the Rebels brought an Ace all the way out here, whatever the civilians are carrying must be important.</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="cloaking">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="AA_SHIP_REBEL_IMAGINATOR_FLARES"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" blue="false" req="cloaking" max_lvl="0" lvl="0">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>This is above our pay grade.</text>
        <event>
			<text>After a time, the Ace turns and leaves, a strange, luminous object attached to its hull. No life-signs are detected from the damaged ship as the Auto-ships descend upon it to strip it to the bone.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_IMAGINATOR_WIN">
    <text>The MFK Ace ship has been dealt with, leaving only the Union vessel. The Auto-ships, having relied upon the Ace to escort them, quickly scatter without weapons to contest you.</text>
    <status type="clear" target="player" system="engines" amount="100"/>
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>Continue...</text>
        <event>
            <text>The civilians aboard the crippled Union ship profess their thanks, though most have nothing to offer. From the crowd, a meek Zoltan in a ragged shirt staggers up to you, presumably the captain's son. "T-thank you... we were trying to figure out what happened to our station, b-but the Rebels wanted everything we had. The least we could do is share something we found. N-never seen anything like it..."</text>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Check their cargo.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>The Zoltan leads you to the cargo bay, opening the doors. The moment they open, a violet light shines out from the spacious room, giving you a momentary headache before your gaze settles on a beam. At least, it looks like a beam. It matches no schematic in your database, its coloration and alien runes betraying not a word of its function. Who knows what the Rebels would want to do with it?</text>
                    <weapon name="AA_BEAM_IMAGINE"/>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Decline.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>"It's okay... that old thing's probably not worth much anyways. I could make it up to you, maybe...?" The Zoltan salutes, wanting to stick around.</text>
                    <crewMember amount="1" class="zoltan">Charles</crewMember>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>




<!-- // RAILGUN // -->
<ship name="AA_SHIP_AUTO_RAILGUN" auto_blueprint="LIST_SHIPS_ESTATE_AUTO">
	<destroyed>
        <text>The powerful Auto-ship is consumed by the fire of your weaponry, letting you snag some useful components and take a closer look at the coordinates you wrote down. You still can't stay for long, though - the city's PDS is still active!</text>
        <quest event="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN"/>
        <autoReward level="MED">scrap</autoReward>
    </destroyed>
</ship>
<event name="AA_EVENT_AUTO_RAILGUN" unique="true">
    <text>You've found an island of calm in a sector that churns with the endless march of machinery. For once, the planet near this beacon is a city world, likely a residential area amongst the shipyards and factories.</text>
    <img back="BACKGROUND" planet="PLANET_POPULATED"/>
    <choice>
        <text>Fly closer.</text>
        <event>
            <text>As you enter the planet's atmosphere, you see the vast expanse of the city below, millions of lights flickering and reflecting off of gray and orange facades. A Rebel city, through and through - it's not likely the people here will be of much help to you.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event>
                    <text>A particularly large complex installed onto the planet, appearing to be a research center, sticks out from many of the buildings. Several Rebel and automated ships, chief among them an automated vessel adorned with crimson paint and a bright logo, swirl around the facility like a flock of vultures as they exchange gigabytes' worth of communications. Listening into whatever this is would likely mean getting close to the building - and getting close to the Rebel force.</text>
                    <ship load="AA_SHIP_AUTO_RAILGUN" hostile="false"/>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Listen in, and risk getting caught.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>You fly close, doing your best to quell the hum of your engines. Splitting your attention between stealth and listening is not easy, but you are able to determine that the station was asking the Rebels to recover a pair of crashed Auto-ships investigating a mysterious shipwreck. Unfortunately, you don't even get the opportunity to read the coordinates you wrote down before the Auto-ship leading the group notices something's off and turns to face you. Even worse, the city's PDS batteries take notice as chatter surges through the facility and the Rebel team!</text>
                            <ship hostile="true"/>
                            <environment type="PDS" target="player"/>
                            <choice hidden="true">
                                <text>Continue...</text>
                                <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <text>This is too dangerous, let's leave.</text>
                        <event/>
                    </choice>
                    <choice hidden="true" req="cloaking" lvl="2" max_group="0">
                        <text>(Upg. Cloaking) Eavesdrop on the meeting.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Not a single Rebel vessel can spot you as your cloaking device hums to life, keeping you hidden from their sensors long enough to get in and get out. The research station was in the middle of hailing a few of the nastier ships in the group to investigate what was most likely a space-time anomaly or another Renegade; though they sent a pair of Auto-ships to investigate, and discovered the remains of a foreign ship, they were unable to escape the planet's ionized atmosphere. Perhaps you could do better than some dinky probes, especially since they leaked the coordinates during the session.</text>
                            <quest event="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN"/>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Ignore the city.</text>
        <event>
			<text>You know better than to get close to a populated area in Rebel territory.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
    </choice>
</event>

<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN">
    <beaconType id="map_icon_quest" global="true">
		<color r="69" g="168" b="235" a="1"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>The location of a crashed ship, whose coordinates you overheard.</unvisitedTooltip>
	</beaconType>
    <img back="BACKGROUND" planet="PLANET_WATER"/>
    <text>You arrive at a beacon clear of ships or debris in orbit, overlooking a large planet shrouded in a blue hue. A number of faint signals flicker from the surface; however, they are in a format you can't read. The atmosphere of the planet is suffused with ion storms and electrical disturbances that further distort the broadcasts, extending out into the space around it.</text>
    <choice>
        <text>Try to investigate the surface.</text>
        <event>
            <text>Though you try to navigate the treacherous atmosphere, it proves wholly untenable to your sensor systems. It will take a great deal of work to find the source of the signal.</text>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Stay and search.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>Although you know the fleet will catch up to you, you press on through the ion storm. Eventually, you are able to locate the source of the signal... though, not without considerable delay.</text>
                    <modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SEARCH"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>This isn't worth it.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>Disappointed at the perpetual storm having absorbed and impeded your attempts, you call off the search. You aren't even left enough time for a routine storage check!</text>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_SLUG">
        <text>(Slug Crew) Have your Slug crew guide you through the ion storm.</text>
        <event>
            <text>With the help of your crew's senses, you are able to steer the ship through the chaos of the storm and down to the distress signal.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SEARCH"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" req="BLUELIST_CREW_SNAIL">
        <text>(Telepathic Shell) Have your Shell crew guide you through the ion storm.</text>
        <event>
            <text>With the help of your crew's senses, you are able to steer the ship through the chaos of the storm and down to the distress signal.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SEARCH"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" req="ADV_SCANNERS">
        <text>(Long-Ranged Scanners) Use your specialized scanners to track the signal.</text>
        <event>
            <text>With your advanced scanning capabilities, you are able to steer the ship through the chaos of the storm and down to the distress signal.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SEARCH"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice req="sensors" lvl="3" hidden="true">
        <text>(Adv. Sensors) Use your powerful sensor system to track the signal.</text>
        <event>
            <text>With your advanced scanning capabilities, you are able to steer the ship through the chaos of the storm and down to the distress signal.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SEARCH"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" req="UPG_AETHER_SCANNERS">
        <text>(Anomaly Detector) Use your specialized scanners to track the signal.</text>
        <event>
            <text>With your Anomaly Detector screaming all sorts of warnings about the source, you are able to steer the ship through the chaos of the storm and down to the distress signal.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SEARCH"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Leave it be.</text>
        <event>
			<text>Who knows, perhaps it could be a trap? It wouldn't be the first time. You steer away from the planet, leaving the calls unanswered.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SEARCH">
    <text>You are able to find the remnants of a massive, crashed ship. Although its make seems human, you cannot tell what faction it belongs to, and its architecture seems very old-school despite how recent the wreck reads to be. Yellow stripes of paint still blaze through the darkness and the tree cover.</text>
    <choice>
        <text>Move in to inspect the wreck.</text>
        <event>
            <text>As you approach the ship, something quickly becomes obvious. Not all of the ship has ceased to function, and a couple of the ship's turrets swivel to face your vessel!</text>
            <choice>
                <text>We can take a few hits!</text>
                <event>
                    <text>The turrets unload a volley of projectiles into your hull! Although rather outdated, using mostly physical shells, they certainly still pack one hell of a punch. It takes some fancy flying and quick thinking to get out of range, your ship dipping below the upper section of the giant wreck to land amongst the trees.</text>
                    <damage amount="8" system="random" effect="breach"/>
                    <damage amount="0" system="random" effect="breach"/>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SUCCESS"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Let's get out of here!</text>
                <event>
                    <text>You punch the engines, leaving the wreck as fast as possible. Artillery shells whistle past your ship as you rocket back off into the atmosphere! Unfortunately, your escapades in navigating the ionic atmosphere have drained you of the time to perform a routine storage check.</text>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice req="weapons" lvl="6" hidden="true">
                <text>(Adv. Weapons) Annihilate the turrets.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>Although the turrets are very fast, your weapons are faster. The turrets cease to exist before they can even fire a shot, leaving you free to inspect the wreck undisturbed.</text>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SUCCESS"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice req="engines" lvl="5" hidden="true">
                <text>(Upg. Engines) Dodge the turrets.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>Although the turrets are very fast, your engines are faster. Each shot from the turrets whizzes by without leaving so much as a scratch on the paint as you home in, leaving you free to inspect the wreck undisturbed.</text>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SUCCESS"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice hidden="true" req="cloaking" lvl="2" max_group="0">
                <text>(Upg. Cloaking) Approach undetected.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>You engage your cloaking device as you fly towards the vessel. The turrets can't even get a lock on your ship, leaving you free to inspect the wreck undisturbed as they jitter around.</text>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SUCCESS"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice hidden="true" req="PDS_DISABLE">
                <text>(Signal Diluter) Approach undetected.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>You engage your signal diluter as you fly towards the vessel. The turrets can't even get a lock on your ship, leaving you free to inspect the wreck undisturbed as they jitter around.</text>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SUCCESS"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Stay in the air.</text>
        <event>
            <text>It's a mystery for sure, but not one that you feel equipped to explore. At least it wasn't a trap. Unfortunately, your escapades in navigating the ionic atmosphere have drained you of the time to perform a routine storage check.</text>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_RAILGUN_SUCCESS">
    <text>Within the bowels of the crashed vessel, you are able to salvage a great deal of old equipment and raw materials. A drop-pod launching system, massive magazine of cryopods, and heavy underside armament suggest this ship was designed for planetary invasion, and its tattered banners with golden highlights and a skull emblem indicate an unknown, though decidedly pompous origin.</text>
    <autoReward level="HIGH">stuff</autoReward>
    <choice>
        <text>Continue...</text>
        <event>
            <text>Though there is already a lot remaining from the wreck, you are able to dig up even more. Unfortunately, you do not have time to salvage all of it - but you find a number of enticing spoils aboard, one kind of which you can claim.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Take the ship's main gun.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>It's big, menacing, and seriously outdated in spite of its masterful construction. After bringing it aboard and giving its leftover ammunition a thorough inspection, you are able to reverse-engineer it. It seems strong enough to punch right through shielding. Perhaps this dinosaur of a gun won't be so useless after all.</text>
                    <autoReward level="HIGH">missiles</autoReward>
                    <weapon name="AA_RAILGUN"/>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Take the ship's firearms.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>In spite of their age, the huge variety of intact weapons and ammunition you find would easily make mincemeat of anything twice your crews' size. Some of them are too large for most crew to wield effectively, up to and including a shoulder-mounted autocannon. Even the more modest of firearms will likely prove to be a great asset to your crew.</text>
                    <autoReward level="MED">scrap</autoReward>
                    <augment name="AA_SUPER_FIREARMS"/>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Take the ship's regalia.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>Each rolled-up banner and blue flag depicting a full view of Old Earth seems to drip with the kind of fervent, dogmatic vigor best befitting a Rebel vessel. Whether this ship used to belong to some Rebel sub-faction, or a different galactic empire entirely, is uncertain. At least they look pretty draped across the galley.</text>
                    <autoReward level="MED">scrap</autoReward>
                    <augment name="AA_XENOPHOBIA"/>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Take a cryopod from the ship.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>The smell coming from this part of the ship is wretched. Although most of the cryopods have malfunctioned, resulting in the deaths of their occupants, a couple of them are still operational. One of them is a human soldier, clad in yellow-striped armor, who seems to have lost their memory of who they were. Judging by the propaganda posters around the ship, that is a good thing.</text>
                    <autoReward level="HIGH">scrap</autoReward>
                    <crewMember amount="1" class="human_soldier">Olofsson</crewMember>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>




<!-- // PASTICHE // -->

<event name="AA_EVENT_ROCK_PASTICHE" unique="true">
    <text>A fleet of Theocracy ships is stationed here, including a few from the blue-clad Inquisition, all clustered around the smoldering wreck of a station. Although it's clear they notice you, for once they don't seem interested in firing at you.</text>
    <customFleet right="false" firing="false" autoDarkening="true">CUSTOM_FLEET_ROCK</customFleet>
    <choice>
        <text>Hail the fleet.</text>
        <event>
            <text>To your surprise, they accept the hail. The Rockman in charge is currently scribbling in a notebook, and an investigation team composed of Orchids and Zoltan scramble about in the background.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event>
                    <text>"Well, then. Renegade, I know your kind. Scrap is what makes your world go round, is it not? We are in the middle of a... very serious... investigation, and your assistance would be appreciated. In return for your aid, we will allow you to remove any valuables from what remains of the wreck once all of the evidence has been collected."</text>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Sure!</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>After they conduct their search and carry a cart of evidence out, the investigation team fills you in on the situation while you scrap the station. A Rockman high up in the Theocracy's hierarchy was performing quite the thunderous speech, but it was cut short when he, and the entirety of his audience, were killed in a bombing that razed the entire station.</text>
                            <choice hidden="true">
                                <text>Continue...</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>Evidence from the remnants of the station implied that the attack was not the work of some Outcast band or internal political matter, but an intervention from another group entirely. Rumors had been circulating around nearby beacons and star systems of a fledgling cult known as the "Gazers," whose preachings were aggressive enough to sway even the most hardened Chrysolic practitioners, and whose converts always wandered around in a drunken stupor. They've been a pain for Rock police to track down until today, and perhaps a Renegade like you could have a better shot at figuring out what happened.</text>
                                    <autoReward level="HIGH">scrap</autoReward>
                                    <quest event="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE"/>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <text>No thank you.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>You decline. The Rockman grunts, but says no more and shuts off the transmission.</text>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                                <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
                            </choice>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Do nothing.</text>
                                <event/>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Not our business.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You figure it's an internal matter, and decide to avoid the Rock ships.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>

<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE" unique="true">
    <beaconType id="map_icon_quest" global="true">
        <color r="69" g="168" b="235" a="1"/>
        <unvisitedTooltip>The purported location of a cult.</unvisitedTooltip>
	</beaconType>
    <text>The investigators' directions led you to a beacon in a mostly unpopulated star system. Although it is quite pretty, you know you have to hurry. In orbit around the planet, you can see a massive space station, likely belonging to the so-called "Gazers." It has been constructed in the shape of a massive eye, staring back from the beacon. There are no other ships anywhere in orbit of the planet or the station, suggesting they are the only inhabitants of the system.</text>
    <img back="BACKGROUND" planet="PLANET_UNPOPULATED"/>
    <choice>
        <text>Check it out.</text>
        <event>
            <text>The station does not open any communications, and the hangar doors seem to have been left open. It remains on its path in orbit, making it easy to intercept and enter. There aren't even drones in the hangar to service your ship, only a few Rock vessels hastily painted over with black paint and an insignia resembling some sort of three-legged creature. It seems almost as if the station is abandoned.</text>
            <jumpEvent>AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER</jumpEvent>
            <choice>
                <text>Explore further.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>The hallways are not very well-maintained, with patches of rust and dust, chips in the wall, and service doors left hanging open. The lights flicker ominously, and the air feels stale enough that you suspect the station's life support is malfunctioning.</text>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>Each corridor feels like a maze unto itself, yet all of them lead to a fairly large ritual chamber with a golden statue of a three-legged entity similar to what was depicted on the Rock ships. Monstrous grins are carved into the walls, some big, some small, and several shelves of scripture are scattered around alongside a variety of crates and boxes. You will not have much time before the air becomes unbreathable, so your inspection of the room will have to be quick and dirty.</text>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Leave the ritual room be.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>You can feel the air getting more and more difficult to breathe with each passing second. You give your crew the order to leave before you all suffocate.</text>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Inspect the boxes.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>Although most of the boxes are full of ritual components and basic supplies, a couple of them are crammed full of ammunition. It seems the Gazers were keeping some ammunition on hand in case the situation spiraled out of control. Even better, however, is another box containing timing mechanisms and other electronics; it's likely they jury-rigged some of their spare missiles to launch an attack on the speech.</text>
                                    <choice hidden="true">
                                        <text>Confiscate the missiles.</text>
                                        <event>
                                            <text>Leaving a couple of them behind as evidence should be enough for the Theocracy investigators, especially since you don't need timers to connect them to. Being in boxes makes it easier to carry them out of the station, though they are still rather heavy. There isn't enough oxygen left to grab much more, but on your way out of the station, there's a few more supplies to take with you as well.</text>
                                            <autoReward level="HIGH">missiles</autoReward>
                                        </event>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Inspect the bookshelves.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>Never would you have expected to see both Chrysolic and Illesctrian scripture right next to each other on a shelf. The cultists have amassed a collection of holy texts from across the galaxy, likely in an attempt to better understand their own religious experiences. This, of course, pales in comparison to the entire shelf above it of black-covered books, stark and practical in their construction - it would take weeks to read through it all, but it could definitely serve as a way to pass the time or find out more about these Gazers.</text>
                                    <choice hidden="true">
                                        <text>Take as many books as you can.</text>
                                        <event>
                                            <text>The books are quite a collection, and it takes your crew a while to find a good way to carry them all. Although the texts on other religions would certainly be worth a decent amount of scrap to the right people, you decide to hang onto the Gazer scripture, as it could prove useful in dealing with these cultists. There isn't enough oxygen left to grab much more, but on your way out of the station, there's a few more supplies to take with you as well.</text>
                                            <autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
                                            <hiddenAug>AA_GAZER_SCRIPTURE</hiddenAug>
                                        </event>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Inspect the statue.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>Underneath the golden monument is a ritual circle, inscribed with inks and carvings that indicate heavy use. Even with the obvious seams and connection points indicating it was assembled piece by piece, it's a miracle the Gazers could fit the statue into the station, especially given how tight the passageways here are. Although something in the back of your head says this thing would be worth a boatload of scrap, making off with it would be no easy task.</text>
                                    <choice req="LIST_CREW_ENGI" hidden="true">
                                        <text>(Engi Crew) Have your Engi help disassemble it.</text>
                                        <event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_INSPECT_STATUE">
                                            <text>As large as the statue is, with precision and expertise, you and your crew concoct a plan to disassemble it for transport. It would still take a while to move, and you suspect the life support here will give out before you can move them all.</text>
                                            <choice req="LIST_CREW_ROCK" hidden="true">
                                                <text>(Rock Crew) Have your Rock help move the pieces.</text>
                                                <event>
                                                    <text>Each piece of the statue is extremely unwieldy and heavy, but your crew's strength helps ease the process. You are able to navigate each piece through the hallways of the station and dump the entire statue aboard before the life support in the room gives out. It's certainly pretty, but it will likely provide a lot more value than just aesthetics.</text>
                                                    <weapon name="AA_GAZER_STATUE"/>
                                                </event>
                                            </choice>
                                            <choice req="BLUELIST_CREW_NO2" hidden="true">
                                                <text>(Anaerobic Crew) It will take a while, but your anaerobic crewmember can handle the lack of oxygen.</text>
                                                <event>
                                                    <text>Each piece of the statue is extremely unwieldy and heavy, and the falling oxygen levels mean that only anaerobic crew can even enter the station after a time. Very slowly, your crew is able to navigate each piece through the hallways of the station and dump the entire statue aboard. It's certainly pretty, but it will likely provide a lot more value than just aesthetics.</text>
                                                    <modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
                                                    <weapon name="AA_GAZER_STATUE"/>
                                                </event>
                                            </choice>
                                            <choice req="DRONE_CONTROL_MEDICAL" hidden="true">
                                                <text>(Medical Drone) Have your drone empower your crew.</text>
                                                <event>
                                                    <text>Each piece of the statue is extremely unwieldy and heavy, but boosting your crew's speed with your medical drone helps ease the process. You are able to navigate each piece through the hallways of the station and dump the entire statue aboard before the life support in the room gives out. It's certainly pretty, but it will likely provide a lot more value than just aesthetics.</text>
                                                    <weapon name="AA_GAZER_STATUE"/>
                                                </event>
                                            </choice>
                                            <choice hidden="true">
                                                <text>The pieces would be too heavy.</text>
                                                <event>
                                                    <text>There's no way to get the statue off of the station. Without much time to spare, you and your crew collect all the supplies they can carry on their person before departing. It's not much, but it's better than nothing.</text>
                                                    <autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
                                                </event>
                                            </choice>
                                        </event>
                                    </choice>
                                    <choice req="LIST_CREW_GHOST" hidden="true">
                                        <text>(Ghost Crew) Have your Ghost help disassemble it.</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_INSPECT_STATUE"/>
                                    </choice>
                                    <choice req="DRONE_CONTROL_REPAIR_CREW" hidden="true">
                                        <text>(Repair Drone) Have your drone help disassemble it.</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_INSPECT_STATUE"/>
                                    </choice>
                                    <choice hidden="true">
                                        <text>There's no way we can disassemble it in time.</text>
                                        <event>
                                            <text>There's no way to get the statue off of the station. Without much time to spare, you and your crew collect all the supplies they can carry on their person before departing. It's not much, but it's better than nothing.</text>
                                            <autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
                                        </event>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>This could be an ambush.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>You stay in the hangar, the murals on the bay wall providing both juicy evidence and an interesting puzzle to decipher as you work on your vessel. Hopefully, the Theocracy investigation team will have enough here to clean up the mess.</text>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                        <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Do nothing.</text>
                        <event/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Stay away.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You avoid the station. Hopefully, just knowing its location will be enough for the Theocracy investigators to clean up the mess.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>

