<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER">
    <text>As you fire up the engines to leave the station, alarms begin to blare in the hangar. A rather large Rock ship sporting a pretty nasty-looking missile launcher begins to rocket towards the bay from the nearby moon, covered in the same black paint as the other docked ships. It seems the station was not abandoned after all...</text>
    <choice>
        <text>Continue...</text>
        <event>
            <text>The ship hails you, its comms hissing to life to reveal a great number of Gazer cultists aboard. They stumble around, as if in a stupor, and speak in an angered, slurred tone. "Trespasser... who... are you..."</text>
            <ship load="AA_SHIP_ROCK_PASTICHE" hostile="false"/>
            <choice>
                <text>We've come to stop this operation.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>"You... dare to stop... what is to come?" The captain and every single one of his crew stares directly at you through the intercom. At once, they all grin in unison, wide, toothy grins that seem like they've... always been there. "He was only... the first pin... in the plan. You will see... you will see..."</text>
                    <ship hostile="true"/>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>We've come to learn more about your ways.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>"You... wish to join us...? Who... how..." They all stand there, their stupor obfuscating your words.</text>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Yes, we wish to join you.</text>
                         <event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_LIAR">
                            <text>"LIAR!" The captain slams his fist into the helm so hard that the control panel cracks underneath it. He, and every single one of his crew, grin at you in unison, wide, toothy grins that seem like they've... always been there. "She told us... we were special. We are the only ones who know, WE ARE THE ONLY ONES SHE LOVES!"</text>
                            <ship hostile="true"/>
                            <choice hidden="true">
                                <text>Continue...</text>
                                <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice>
                        <text>No, idiot! We've come to kill you.</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>The Rockman at the helm begins to laugh, a maniacal laugh that echoes through the entire ship. He, and every single one of his crew, grin at you in unison, wide, toothy grins that seem like they've... always been there. "In time... you will see... who the real idiot... is!"</text>
                            <ship hostile="true"/>
                            <choice hidden="true">
                                <text>Continue...</text>
                                <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                    <choice req="AA_GAZER_SCRIPTURE">
                        <text>(Gazer Scripture) Claim you've been reading their books.</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_LIAR"/>
                    </choice>
                    <choice req="LIST_CREW_ROCK">
                        <text>(Rock Crew) Have your Rockman talk them down.</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_LIAR"/>
                    </choice>
                    <choice req="LIST_CREW_ZOLTAN">
                        <text>(Zoltan Crew) Have your Zoltan talk them down.</text>
                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_LIAR"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>I don't know why we're here.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>The Rockman at the helm begins to laugh, a maniacal laugh that echoes through the entire ship. He, and every single one of his crew, grin at you in unison, wide, toothy grins that seem like they've... always been there. "Then you must... get out... of our way! We must continue to follow the plan!"</text>
                    <ship hostile="true"/>
                    <choice hidden="true">
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice req="LIST_CREW_ELDRITCH" hidden="true">
                <text>(Eldritch Crew) We have come for an offering.</text>
                <event>
                    <text>As soon as your unusual crewmember takes the stand, the Rockmen all stand up straight, whatever mental haze they are feeling directing itself towards the viewscreen. They all drop to their knees in prayer, muttering ancient words that you do not understand. The ship gives you everything they have, in addition to even more loot set aside in hidden compartments on the station! After the haul is brought aboard, your crew even shows you leaked coordinates to the supposed birthplace of their religion.</text>
                    <autoReward level="HIGH">scrap</autoReward>
                    <weapon name="GIFTLIST_ROCK"/>
                    <crewMember amount="1" class="rock_commando"/>
                    <quest event="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL"/>
                </event>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_KILL">
    <text>With the strange Rock ship defeated, you can finally leave the beacon without further interruption. They had a lot of scrap and resources to give, likely an offering or resources to further a plan. Although you expect the Theocracy will be here soon to clean the rest up, you can't help but feel that this mystery goes deeper than you thought...</text>
    <autoReward level="HIGH">scrap</autoReward>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_ESCAPE">
    <text>"Must... go... home..." With the Gazer ship running on fumes, the crew at least have enough sense left in their minds to attempt an escape, presumably to what they see as safer territory. Their engines sputter to life!</text>
    <clearTriggeredEvent name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_TRIGGER"/> 
    <escape/>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_GOTAWAY">
    <text>The Gazer ship has escaped. Although the Theocracy likely won't be very happy, they'll at least have a station full of evidence to work out the case on their own. This "home," however, could be anywhere, and they left very little to go off of.</text>
    <choice hidden="true" req="FTL_JUMPER">
		<text>(Adv. Navigation) Track the ship's jump signature.</text>
		<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_GOTAWAY_FOLLOW">
            <text>Sniffing out the ship's jump signature allows your systems to reconstruct the path it took across the stars. Although the coordinates it offers seem rather strange, and some sort of interference radiates from the beacon in question, it's the only lead you have if you want to pursue this mystery to its end. You scoop up some loose scrap shaken from their battered vessel, and prepare to leave.</text>
            <autoReward level="LOW">scrap</autoReward>
            <quest event="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL"/>
        </event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="ADV_SCANNERS">
		<text>(Long-Ranged Scanners) Track the ship's jump signature.</text>
		<event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_GOTAWAY_FOLLOW"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="sensors" lvl="3">
		<text>(Adv. Sensors) Track the ship's jump signature.</text>
		<event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_ENCOUNTER_GOTAWAY_FOLLOW"/>
	</choice>
    	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>There's nothing we can do.</text>
		<event>
            <text>Although they may have escaped, there's at least a bit of loose scrap from the beating their ship took. You are able to squeeze in a salvage mission before the time comes to leave.</text>
            <autoReward level="LOW">scrap</autoReward>
        </event>
	</choice>
</event>

