<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL" unique="true">
    <beaconType id="map_icon_cultist" global="true">
		<color r="255" g="0" b="0" a="1.0"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>The location the Gazers jumped to.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
		<undiscoveredTooltip>An unvisited location.</undiscoveredTooltip>
	</beaconType>
    <text>You've made it to the presumed "home" of the Gazers. The stars here seem to be dimmer than usual, and there are no other ships at the beacon. It feels... quiet. Too quiet.</text>
    <img back="BACK_EVENT_STARS_SPARSE" planet="NONE"/>
    <choice>
        <text>Stay at the beacon.</text>
        <event>
            <text>The oppressive darkness around you seems to blanket your ship in its cold embrace. It feels like the lights are dimming, their colors separating more and more the longer you remain here. Nothing seems to be here, though the sense of fear is quite palpable...</text>
            <playMusic>nothing</playMusic>
            <changeBackground>VICTORY_TRUE</changeBackground>
            <choice>
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event>
                    <text>As it seems the darkness can't get any thicker, a roiling fog of shadow that threatens to swallow you, your ship, and your crew whole, you can make out the outline of another vessel. Blacker than the darkest night, its paradoxical highlights splitting into hues of red and blue at the corners, the mere sight of it is enough to give you a splitting headache for reasons that you can't explain. The text on each screen of your ship begins to smear, each visual warping to display maddening grins that stare into your very soul, whispers echoing in the back of your mind that direct you to do everything you don't want to do.</text>
                    <ship load="AA_BOSS_SIREN_PASTICHE" hostile="false"/>
                    <variable name="loc_protomv_drive_block" op="set" val="1"/>
                    <choice>
                        <text>Continue...</text>
                        <event>
                            <text>As the maddening darkness draws closer, both infinitely captivating and utterly repulsive in every possible way, you see visions of infinite futures that could be, and infinite pasts that led you to this moment. The ship does not hail, but the message of its occupants, a message everyone on your ship sees in their mind's eye, is clearer than the purest pools of water. You must join them, and the Rockmen who have dedicated themselves to them, and submit to eternal revelry in a madness so deep that it will swallow you forever.</text>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Join them.</text>
                                <event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL_LOSE">
                                    <text>Their ship slowly begins to creep up beside yours. Although you can feel your legs slowly trudging below you, the last few cognizant neurons in your mind scream at you to stop, that this is wrong, that you still have a mission to do. Their cries are but whispers amongst the comforting thoughts filling your head...</text>
                                    <choice>
                                        <text>Wait, this is wrong!</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL_FIGHT"/>
                                    </choice>
                                    <choice>
                                        <text>Relax, and let your worries slip away.</text>
                                        <event>
                                            <text>In what feels like an instant, your last feelings of terror are overcome with a feeling of absolute bliss, your vision hazy and your thoughts pulsing in rhythm with the heralds of a new dawn. Your crew follow suit, walking in lockstep with each minute that passes. Your vessel begins to unravel, revealing a bridge into infinite blackness that you are all too comfortable to walk down, forever and ever, as the secrets of the Multiverse fill your mind, melting your mind until there is naught left but your desire to serve the gods of this world. You are one with your new masters, and it feels good.</text>
                                            <lose text="Forever enslaved to a being beyond your comprehension, you traveled the Multiverse as a chained captain."/>
                                        </event>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                            <choice>
                                <text>Resist the pull.</text>
                                <event>
                                    <text>Why don't you want to join them, you hear in the back of your mind? All of your worries can drift away. That silly little Flagship, that funny little Rebel fleet, your fears of the health and well-being of your crew, or of being torn to shreds by giant alien spiders... all of it can become irrelevant, for as long as you live. Join them.</text>
                                    <choice>
                                        <text>Join them.</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL_LOSE"/>
                                    </choice>
                                    <choice>
                                        <text>Continue to resist the pull.</text>
                                        <event load="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL_FIGHT"/>
                                    </choice>
                                </event>
                            </choice>
                        </event>
                    </choice>
                </event>
            </choice>
            <choice>
            <text>Run!</text>
            <event>
                <text>Fearful, you order your crew to punch the engines and escape the general vicinity of the system. You do not want to tangle with whatever this is!</text>
                <changeBackground>BACKGROUND</changeBackground>
                <playMusic/>
                <choice>
                    <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                    <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <text>Do nothing.</text>
                    <event/>
                </choice>
            </event>
        </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Get out of here!</text>
        <event>
            <text>Space normally doesn't look like this. With a lingering sense of dread tingling down your spine, you order your crew to move on after the usual storage check procedures. You do not want to tangle with whatever this is!</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL_FIGHT">
    <text>The fuzz from your mind begins to dissipate, the comforting whispers beginning to recede as the full might of the abomination before you becomes apparent. A mix of homegrown weaponry and guns pillaged from other vessels adorns its hull, and the cultists from the Gazer craft you met earlier are visible through your comms feed alongside massive, jet-black, three-legged creatures of unknown origin. The ship emits an unearthly roar as its thrusters hiss black fire and grainy smoke, and its highlights nearly blind you with their captivating, migraine-inducing splendor. There is only one way out of this, and that is to fight for your life!</text>
    <ship hostile="true"/>
    <playMusic>ancient2</playMusic>
    <triggeredEvent name="AA_TRIGGER_BOSS_SIREN_PASTICHE_HAZARDS" event="AA_BOSS_SIREN_PASTICHE_HAZARDS" time="35" thisFight="true" loops="999999"> <!-- Start hazard cycling -->
        <warningMessage id="warning_newhazard" x="444" y="46" time="5.0" centerText="true" flash="true" sound="surgeWarning" useWarningLine="true"/>
    </triggeredEvent>
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>Continue...</text>
        <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="AA_EVENT_QUEST_PASTICHE_FINAL_WIN">
    <text>The ship seems to writhe in several impossible directions, and you rapidly black out...</text>
    <removeHazards/>
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>Continue...</text>
        <event>
            <text>When you finally come to, you see the rest of your crew also pulling themselves off of the floor. Your ship's systems begin to sputter back online, revealing the smoldering wreckage of an enemy ship you barely recognize. Its hull is darker than the depths of space, and it bears runic marks across its exterior that once glowed with a disorienting light. Its scrap, though relatively low in quantity and still crackling with an energy you do not understand, is sure to be extremely valuable thanks to its mysterious source.</text>
            <autoReward level="HIGH">scrap</autoReward>
            <changeBackground>BACKGROUND</changeBackground>
            <variable name="loc_protomv_drive_block" op="set" val="0"/>
            <playMusic/>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event>
